Now that present 🎁 time is over let’s get down to the real sh%t….

I love being American but we have commercialized the sh%t out of holidays and it has many of us forgetting why we are celebrating in the first place (I’m guilty of this too)

I love being with my family, eating, laughing, loving, praying, and eating some more but it’s important for us to remember what Jesus Christ means to us.

To me, he is the embodiment of strength, forgiveness, compassion, faith, courage, and LOVE at its core even in a world filled with chaos, going through so much destruction, pain, depression, greed, and even slavery and genocide.

To me, he represents the connection to Gods love that is in every one of us.

I have been passionate about leadership since I was a little boy. It’s the reason why I have devoted my life to creating and inspiring leaders around the world.

To me, the ultimate example of a leader is Jesus Christ aka Yeshua.

If you read about Jesus (something I am even more committed to this year), you realize he never looked to achieve being a “leader” … he was about being a servant of the people. 

He didn’t want or need the spotlight, or fame, or instagram followers, or even notoriety. His words were…

“Anyone who wants to be first must be the very last, and the servant of all.” Jesus wasn’t trying to replace greatness or diminish ambition, he was only giving us a new definition of greatness, which is servanthood and stewardship.

He epitomized what it meant to be human. He didn’t envy but wanted to awaken the greatness in others. He was humble yet exemplified strength even when caused suffering. He sacrificed his life for us all to realize the importance of equality, forgiveness, unity, love.

A servant leader, son of God, who stood with honor for all of humanity.

May we all RISE this year with the power of Christ within us to reach our fullest expression of what it means to create an impact and legacy for generations to come.

20 Things I learned being a Serial Entrepreneur For 20 Years

1. Entrepreneurship is not a linear path, embrace the journey.

2. Always be ready to seize the moment, you never know when a timely opportunity will appear.

3. Failure is a part of the process, you only truly fail if you choose to quit.

4. Never stop learning. Be obsessed with growing daily.

5. Understand your unique gifts and master your craft. Delegate the rest.

6. You can go far as a lone wolf, but much farther with a wolf pack.

7. Lead by example.

8. Hard work comes before the dream. Outwork your self doubt.

9. Every obstacle is an opportunity to up-level.

10. I never thought I would say this 10 years ago but self-love is a cheat code.

11. If you want to build a sustainable, scalable, and exit-able business become obsessed at measuring results.

12. You must be convicted in your vision and enroll their vision into yours.

13. Time is either your enemy or your most cherished tool - use it wisely.

14. Discipline is your destiny.

15. Your success is directly correlated to your ability to focus.

16. The new wave entrepreneur is a compassionate leader that gets shit done.

17. You can know every piece of business knowledge but it comes down to what you believe about yourself. Change your mindset, change your beliefs, change your life.

18. Learn the art of contemplation.

19. You are the author of your story, it matters - own it.

20. Follow your heart. Listen to your intuition. And take the time to do research.
